This idea may also be used on the Saturn concept: The cooling zone or reaction zone, where wax deposition occurs is periodically exposed to a sharp heat pulse. As earlier mentioned, this heat pulse can be generated either:



    

by direct electrical heat or by installing a heating cable (either inductive or resistive) as shown in FIG. 4, or;

